        "message": "LU-5969 lustreapi: change license from GPL to LGPL\n\nThis is an patch to update the copyright license of the liblustreapi\nlibrary from GPL to LGPL. This will simplify the use of liblustreapi\nby third party applications (e.g. non-GPL HSM copytools, Lustre-aware\nuser applications or libraries, etc) and distribution of same in both\nsource and binary form.  In particular, liblustreapi.c, lustreapi.h\nand supporting files and headers libcfs_kernelcomm.h, l_ioctl.c,\nlustre_user.h, and lustre_ioctl.h will have their license changed.\n\nOther files in the library (liblustreapi_hsm.c, liblustreapi_json.c,\nliblustreapi_layout.c, liblustreapi_lease.c, lustreapi_internal.h)\nalready have explicit LGPL headers.\n\nThis patch requires signoff from all organizations that have copyright\non these files by virtue of making changes to the code, as recorded by\nthe commit records after the Lustre 2.0 release.\n\nCopyright assignment was previously required for all contributions to\nCluster File Systems, Sun Microsystems, and Oracle for Lustre 2.0 and\nearlier.  The Oracle Lustre copyright of the liblustreapi.c code was\nlater assumed by Xyratex/Seagate, so a signoff by Seagate is enough\nto cover all earlier contributions.\n\nAuthors of patches to these files since Lustre 2.0:\n\nBull\n- Sebastien Buisson <sebastien.buisson@bull.net>\n- Gregoire Pichon <gregoire.pichon@bull.net>\nCommissariat a l'Energie Atomique et aux Energies Alternatives\n- Aurelien Degremont <aurelien.degremont@cea.fr>\n- Jacques-Charles Lafoucriere <jc.lafoucriere@cea.fr>\n- Henri Doreau <henri.doreau@cea.fr>\nCray\n- Frank Zago <fzago@cray.com>\nData Direct Networks\n- Li Xi <lixi@ddn.com>\n- Swapnil Pimpale <spimpale@ddn.com>\nIndiana University\n- Joshua Walgenbach <jjw@iu.edu>\nIntel/Whamcloud\n- Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\n- Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\n- Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\n- Bobi Jam <bobijam@whamcloud.com>\n- Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\n- Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\n- Hongchao Zhang <hongchao.zhang@whamcloud.com>\n- James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\n- Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\n- Johann Lombardi <johann@whamcloud.com>\n- John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\n- Keith Mannthey <keith.mannthey@intel.com>\n- Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\n- Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\n- Michael MacDonald <michael.macdonald@intel.com>\n- Minh Diep <mdiep@whamcloud.com>\n- Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\n- Richard Henwood <rhenwood@whamcloud.com>\n- Wang Di <di.wang@intel.com>\n- Yang Sheng <ys@whamcloud.com>\nLawrence Livermore National Laboratory\n- Christopher J. Morrone <morrone2@llnl.gov>\n- Ned Bass <bass6@llnl.gov>\n- Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nOak Ridge National Laboratory\n- James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\n- Matt Ezell <ezellma@ornl.gov>\nSeagate/Xyratex\n- Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\nTexas Advance Computing Center\n- John L. Hammond <jhammond@tacc.utexas.edu>\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If40fb44d57c91a9c35882eeee7ec6f2772586631\n"
